question: The heats of combustion for three compounds with the molecular formula $\ce{C_5H_8}$ are as follows: cyclopentene, $\Delta H_{comb}=-1027\ kcal\ mol^{-1}$; 1,4-pentadiene, $\Delta H_{comb}=-1042\ kcal\ mol^{-1}$; and 1-pentyne, $\Delta H_{comb}=-1052\ kcal\ mol^{-1}$​. Explain in terms of relative stability and bond strengths.
